    "PARFITLY": "Perfectly. [Obs.] Chaucer.",
    "PARFLECHE": "A kind of rawhide consisting of hide, esp. of the buffalo,which has been soaked in crude wood-ash lye to remove the hairs, andthen dried.",
    "PARFOCAL": "With the lower focal points all in the same plane; -- said ofsets of eyepieces so mounted that they may be interchanged withoutvarying the focus of the instrument (as a microscope or telescope)with which they are used.",
    "PARGASITE": "A dark green aluminous variety of amphibole, or hornblende.",
    "PARGEBOARD": "See Bargeboard.",
    "PARGETER": "A plasterer. Johnson.",
