    "PASSING": "The act of one who, or that which, passes; the act of going byor away. Passing bell, a tolling of a bell to announce that a soul ispassing, or has passed, from its body (formerly done to invokeprayers for the dying); also, a tolling during the passing of afuneral procession to the grave, or during funeral ceremonies. Sir W.Scott. Longfellow.",
