    "PERCEPTION": "The faculty of perceiving; the faculty, or peculiar part, ofman's constitution by which he has knowledge through the medium orinstrumentality of the bodily organs; the act of apperhendingmaterial objects or qualities through the senses; -- distinguishedfrom conception. Sir W. Hamilton.Matter hath no life nor perception, and is not conscious of its ownexistence. Bentley.",
