    "PERPETUAL": "Neverceasing; continuing forever or for an unlimited time;unfailing; everlasting; continuous.Unto the kingdom of perpetual night. Shak.Perpetual feast of nectared sweets. Milton.Circle of perpetual apparition, or occultation. See under Circle.-- Perpetual calendar, a calendar so devised that it may be adjustedfor any month or year.-- Perpetual curacy (Ch. of Eng.), a curacy in which all the tithesare appropriated, and no vicarage is endowed. Blackstone.-- Perpetual motion. See under Motion.-- Perpetual screw. See Endless screw, under Screw.",
