    "PHALANGOIDEA": "A division of Arachnoidea, including the daddy longlegs orharvestman (Phalangium) and many similar kinds. They have long,slender, many-jointed legs; usually a rounded, segmented abdomen; andchelate jaws. They breathe by tracheæ. Called also Phalangides,Phalangidea, Phalangiida, and Opilionea.",
    "PHALANSTERE": "A phalanstery.",
    "PHALANSTERIAN": "Of or pertaining to phalansterianism.",
    "PHALANX": "A body of heavy-armed infantry formed in ranks and files closeand deep. There were several different arrangements, the phalanxvarying in depth from four to twenty-five or more ranks of men. \"Incubic phalanx firm advanced.\" Milton.The Grecian phalanx, moveless as a tower. Pope.",
    "PHALAROPE": "Any species of Phalaropus and allied genera of small wadingbirds (Grallæ), having lobate toes. They are often seen far fromland, swimming in large flocks. Called also sea goose.",
