    "PIPIT": "Any one of numerous species of small singing birds belonging toAnthus and allied genera, of the family Motacillidæ. They stronglyresemble the true larks in habits, colors, and the great length ofthe hind claw. They are, therefore, often called titlarks, and pipitlarks.",
