    "PLUG": "A block of wood let into a wall, to afford a hold for nails.Fire plug, a street hydrant to which hose may be attached. [U. S.] --Hawse plug (Naut.), a plug to stop a hawse hole.-- Plug and feather. (Stone Working) See Feather, n., 7.-- Plug centerbit, a centerbit ending in a small cylinder instead ofa point, so as to follow and enlarge a hole previously made, or toform a counterbore around it.-- Plug rod (Steam Eng.) , a rod attached to the beam for workingthe valves, as in the Cornish engine.-- Plug valve (Mech.), a tapering valve, which turns in a case likethe plug of a faucet.",
