    "PREDICROTIC": "A term applied to the pulse wave sometimes seen in a pulsecurve or sphygmogram, between the apex of the curve and the dicroticwave.The predicrotic or tidal wave is best marked in a hard pulse, i. e.,where the blood pressure is high. Landois & Stirling.",
