    "PSYCHOPHYSICAL": "Of or pertaining to psychophysics; involving the action ormutual relations of the psychical and physical in man. Psychophysicaltime (Physiol.), the time required for the mind to transform asensory impression into a motor impulse. It is an important part ofphysiological or reaction time. See under Reaction.",
